# Rust Test Lua Sources

When adding or changing Rust integration tests for Lua semantics:

- Prefer inline Lua source strings inside the test case.
- Use `setup_single_file(src, ...)` for one-file cases.
- Use `setup_workspace(&[(filename, src), ...])` for multi-file cases.
- Do not depend on `tests/lua-root/` or `tests/lua-root2/` for a semantic regression test; those directories are manual end-to-end workspaces and may be edited during debugging.
- Use external Lua fixtures only when the behavior under test is fixture loading, real directory scanning, workspace layout, or compatibility with an existing stable fixture.
- If an external fixture is necessary, avoid assertions that depend on mutable manual-test line numbers or incidental file content.
